The Commission has got it right overall , i.e. in extending codecision to the entire legislative field , but this kind of all - encompassing statement comes to nothing , as the co - rapporteurs observe , when we actually move on to definitions and specifics . We then find that if we apply the criteria proposed by the Commission we move into a grey area and are faced with a choice which , as the co - rapporteurs state , is both restrictive and lacking in innovation . 
